title: Claude Monet Water Lilies Tote
description:
Tote developed from Claude Monet’s Water Lilies, 1906, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Adapted from Water Lilies by Claude Monet (French, 1840–1926). Now you can enjoy this masterwork every day.  Made of polyester with a zip top closure and two internal pockets.

  • Dimensions: 17 x 11.5 x 5.5 in.
  • Material: Matt polyester satin.
  • Zippered Closure, internal pocket.
